The paper proposes a deep learning approach for low-dose X-ray CT reconstruction, which involves the use of a convolutional neural network (CNN) and wavelet transform. This work falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it involves image processing and analysis. Additionally, the use of deep learning algorithms and neural networks suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses the use of residual learning architecture, which is a technique used in information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the evaluation of the proposed algorithm involves rigorous testing and comparison with existing methods, which suggests that it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) category.
